body:
The current version of `basetype` doesn't throw an informative error message when the input type has 0 size, and it can throw an error when the input type contains one or more fields with zero size (e.g., `ForwardDiff.Dual{Nothing, Float64, 0}`). This PR fixes both of these issues. It also gets rid of the `basetype` method defined for `NamedTuple`, which is unnecessary because the fields of a `NamedTuple` are the same as the fields of the underlying `Tuple`.

Note that this does not add the ability to have `basetype` return something other than an `AbstractFloat`. That will require further changes.

@simonbyrne @jakebolewski
